- The string parameter `s` must not be null and must consist of binary characters '0' and '1'.
- The integer array parameter `queries` must not be null and must have a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 100000.
- Each element in the integer array parameter `queries` must be an array of length 2 containing integers within the range of 0 to 10^9.
- The integer array result `ans` must have the same length as the integer array parameter `queries`.
- Each element in the integer array result `ans` must be an array of length 2 containing integers representing the endpoints of the shortest substring that satisfies the given conditions or [-1, -1] if no such substring exists.